/*
 * Guide lines (Experiment 2b) — CSS stacked-gradient technique
 * (@replit/codemirror-indentation-markers), see
 * docs/research/07-decoration-experiments-plan.md. decorations.ts merges a
 * `--to-guides` custom property (a comma-joined list of repeating-linear-
 * gradient layers, one per active ancestor depth) into the same line that
 * already carries `--to-depth` — a single `::before` renders every layer
 * as one background, O(1) DOM nodes regardless of depth.
 *
 * Only ever applied to `to-decor-block` lines (headings/paragraphs), never
 * `to-decor-atom`/`to-decor-list` — a confirmed structural limitation, not
 * an oversight: those use `margin-left` (Experiment 1's own fix for the
 * padding-never-moves-the-box bug), which shifts the LINE'S OWN BOX, so
 * any background painted inside it is clipped to a canvas starting to the
 * right of a shallower ancestor's own column — no `background-position`
 * value can paint further left than a box's own left edge. `padding-left`
 * (used for block lines) never shifts the box, so a block line's own box
 * always starts at the same x regardless of depth — the same assumption
 * @replit/codemirror-indentation-markers relies on for plain code
 * indentation (rendered via leading whitespace, so the line's box never
 * moves either), but one this project's own tree-based, mixed padding-
 * and-margin indentation only holds for block lines, not atoms/lists.
 *
 * Neither `!important` nor Obsidian's own ancestor-chain specificity
 * workaround is needed here (unlike padding-left/margin-left above):
 * `background`/`position` on `.cm-line` aren't contested by any of
 * Obsidian's own rules — confirmed live, not assumed (see the experiment's
 * results writeup for how this was verified).
 */
.markdown-source-view.mod-cm6 .cm-content > .cm-line.to-decor-guides {
  position: relative;
}

.markdown-source-view.mod-cm6 .cm-content > .cm-line.to-decor-guides::before {
  content: '';
  position: absolute;
  top: 0;
  left: 0;
  right: 0;
  bottom: 0;
  background: var(--to-guides);
  opacity: 0.6;
  pointer-events: none;
  z-index: -1;
}

